title: For Sale:  Colt Trooper Mark-V 4" Blue .357 Magnum
postcontent: Here is your chance to buy a Colt that is sometimes called the "Poorman's Python"...  The Colt Trooper Mark-V is the predecessor to the King Cobra and is less expensive then both the King Cobra & the Python.  Mark-V's have exactly the same trigger and hammer system as the King Cobra, Anaconda and Diamondback.  This revolver is equipped with Target Grips, Hammer and Trigger.  This Colt has had a little trigger work done so it is quite quick and smooth with a SA pull right at a 2lb and just under 10lbs in DA.  The timing is very good and is exactly what Colt designed it to be for a Trooper Mark-V which is exactly the same as the King Cobra.  Hey S&W guys... The lockup of the cylinder is not the same as a Smith so don't expect it to be.  (It's not bad, it's just different).  The only real difference between the Mark-V and the King Cobra is the exterior finish (Mark-V's didn't come in a Stainless Finish).  Mark-V's don't have a full length lower barrel lug either but they do have a vented top rib like the Python.  As with all higher-end Colts this revolver has adjustable sights.  I'm selling the 4" revolver, which is in excellent condition,  for $775.00 (Firm).  No Trades please.  My asking price is fair as 2 have sold on Gun Broker for over $900 in the past week and those buyers have to pay shipping and FFL fees.  Call/Text Rick 5O5*6IO*529I

title: For Sale:  Walker Colt by Uberti with accessories! Most POWERFUL cap & ball ever!
postcontent:
I have a used, very good condition Uberti Walker Colt that I am selling so that I can buy a 3D printer. 
This 4 1/2 lb. revolver is a real behemoth with a 9" barrel that'll hurl a .44 caliber round ball out at over 1100 fps! Without going through an FFL, you get six shots of serious firepower - followed by a lot of cleaning ;)
My reproduction cap & ball will be sold with the following accessories:

1 near-full box of round balls (about 80 I'd guess)
1 nipple wrench 
1 opened tube of bore butter
1 unopened tin of 100 No. 11 percussion caps

All you need to start shooting is some powder!
I've gotten a lot of good use out of it and taken as many hi-resolution pictures as I can to show its condition (armslist limits to 3 pics/4MB). I never shot it with 60 grain loads and always took care of it, of course, it is a used black powder revolver. It has some light scratches that you can see in the picture but it's in good condition and I really would like to hold onto it.
This isn't one of those cheap knock-offs made of soft metals - this is an Italian made Uberti which costs $439 new (http://www.uberti.com/1847-walker-revolver). I'm selling mine with all the accessories for only $295!
If you have any questions, feel free to contact me. I'd be willing to drive up to an hour to deliver it to a public place, where we can meet. No deliveries to NJ - know your local laws.
Firearm sold as-is, buyer assumes all responsibility.
You won't find another little set-up like this for less than three hundred dollars. It's a lot of fun, it's accurate, throws out a ton of smoke and has minimal recoil due to it's weight.
Good luck!

title: For Sale:  Springfield Armory XD-9 High Capacity Sub-Compact
postcontent:
I have only fired right at 100 rounds through this SA XD-9 pistol.  It is almost like brand new.  It shoots great and, obviously, it is a very high quality carry pistol.  It comes with a flush fitting 13 round magazine as well as the form fitting extended 16 round magazine from Springfield.  I have sold many firearms here and everyone always tells me that the firearm they purchase is far nicer than I described.  Literally, I ran 100 rounds through this pistol to break it in and make sure everything works fine for it to be a carry pistol, cleaned it and put it away.  I've never carried it.  However, included is the XD "gear", which includes a Springfield holster, Springfield double magazine holder and Springfield loading tool.  Obviously, the lock, manual and very high quality Springfield original case are included as well.

If you are not familiar with the Springfield eXtreme Duty pistols, just Google them. (the XD in the name is for 'extreme duty')  These pistols are well known for being ultimately reliable, extremely durable and very accurate.  I have collected firearms for many years and I would say that this pistol compares very well with a Glock 26 except that you get 13 rounds (as opposed to 10 with the G26) along with the option of having 16 rounds with the included higher capacity magazine.  Some people have strong feelings either way, but having shot both, they seem to shoot pretty well the same to me.  I simply have way too many firearms and am reducing the size of my collection.
